The paper discusses the use of Triple Modular Redundancy (TMR) to mitigate Single Event Upsets (SEUs) in SRAM-based FPGAs, which are commonly used in the aerospace industry. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Embedded Systems (cs.ET) or Architecture (cs.AR) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of probabilistic model checking to analyze TMR partitioning at an early design stage, which suggests that it may also belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Software Engineering (cs.SE), or Electromagnetics (cs.EM) sub-categories.
